name: Charlie Rohrer
bio:
Charlie Rohrer dropped out of college to tell jokes. Comedy just seemed more viable than a bachelor's degree in Fine Arts. Growing up the black sheep of an enormous Irish family in the South Suburbs of Chicago, his comedy mostly comes from self-reflection, tales from his awkward childhood, and his unique view on everyday life.

He co-producers a very successful, independent show in Chicago called "Congrats on Your Success," and has performed at Zanie’s, Chicago Underground Comedy, Gilda’s Laughfest, and more.
